# Vibe Coding Rules

## Architecture
- Use Atomic Design only for the design-system layer.
- Organize application code by feature and concern.
- Prefer components under 150 lines; split by responsibility, not by arbitrary count.
- Prefer functions under 50 lines when practical.
- Extract stateful and business logic into hooks or services.
- Avoid file explosion and empty wrapper abstractions.

## React / Next.js
- Fix async waterfalls first.
- Reduce bundle size second.
- Prefer server components where possible.
- Push client components to the leaves.
- Avoid oversized client bundles and cascading `useEffect` fetch chains.

## Security
- No custom production auth.
- Use short-lived access tokens and rotated refresh tokens.
- Validate every input with typed schemas.
- Enforce authorization server-side.
- Use strict CORS, security headers, rate limits, and CSRF protection where applicable.
- Validate uploads by allow-list, size, and content/signature.
- No secrets in code, logs, comments, fixtures, or commits.

## Tooling
- Code must pass formatting, linting, type checks, tests, and secret scanning.
- Do not treat `npm audit fix` as magic.
- Prefer reviewed remediation over blind auto-fix.
- If deviating from a rule, add `SEC-DEBT:` with a concise reason.
